    "client_msg_id": "8dec849c-f05b-4465-889a-29d8c86a2d90",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "Great find Dan!\n&gt; One goal is to get rid of the idea of \"control flow\" passing from one object to another, and instead have each advertize what it needs or what it's intent is, and let a kernel do the \"wiring\" automatically. Objects can thus run in parallel, or even in different machines, and the communication / execution is the same.\n\nSounds a bit like the 'wish' idea in Dynamicland:\n<https://rsnous.com/posts/notes-from-dynamicland-geokit/#background-on-realtalk>",
